{
  "texts": [
    "Which is the most likely place where Thomas lost it?\"",
    "The present author's experiments have indicated that GPT-3.5 provides false answers to this task when asked with Input-Output prompting.",
    "However, the responses turned out to be correct when asked with ToT-prompting.",
    "GPT-4 sometimes implements a similar method without being prompted, but often it does not do so automatically.",
    "A previous version of ToT was known as Prompt Ensembling (or DiVeRSe: Diverse Verifier on Reasoning Steps), which worked with a three-step process: (i) Using multiple prompts to generate diverse answers; (ii) using a verifier to distinguish good from bad responses; and (iii) using a verifier to check the correctness of the reasoning steps (Li et al., 2023)."
  ]
}